   <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The slopes and SDs are listed both as the areal loss each year and as the percentage of the ice cover lost each decade. The R column gives the ratio of the slope magnitude for the areal loss to its SD, as a rough indicator of statistical significance, both for the 40-y record and for the 36-y record. Statistical significance at the 95% level or above is indicated in the R column by italics and statistical significance at the 99% level or above is indicated by boldface.</p>
